iaging E2E failures* from <run_url|run #ID>...`\\n\\n**After Claude runs** (new step at the end):\\n- New step: \\\"Notify Slack: triage complete\\\"\\n- Reads `triage-summary.json` written by Claude (see below)\\n- Posts a summary message with links to PRs and issues created\\n- Uses `if: always()` so it posts even if Claude's step fails (with a fallback \\\"triage failed\\\" message)\\n\\nWorkflow step structure:\\n```yaml\\n      - name: Notify Slack - triage started\\n        uses: slackapi/slack-github-action@91efab103c0de0a537f72a35f6b8cda0ee76bf0a\\n        with:\\n          webhook: ${{ secrets.E2E_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL }}\\n          webhook-type: incoming-webhook\\n          payload: # \\\"Claude is triaging...\\\" message\\n\\n      - name: Run triage\\n        # ... existing Claude step ...\\n\\n      - name: Build Slack summary\\n        if: always()\\n        id: summary\\n        # Read triage-summary.json, format for Slack, or fallback message\\n\\n      - name: Notify Slack - triage complete\\n        if: always()\\n        uses: slackapi/slack-github-action@91efab103c0de0a537f72a35f6b8cda0ee76bf0a\\n        with:\\n          webhook: ${{ secrets.E2E_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL }}\\n          webhook-type: incoming-webhook\\n          payload: # Summary message with PR/issue links\\n```\\n\\n### 2. `.claude/skills/e2e-triage/SKILL.md` — Add triage-summary.json output\\n\\nAdd to Step 7 (Summary Report): Claude must write a `triage-summary.json` file in the artifact directory with:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"actions\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"test\\\": \\\"TestCheckpointCreated\\\",\\n      \\\"agents\\\": [\\\"claude-code\\\", \\\"opencode\\\"],\\n      \\\"classification\\\": \\\"flaky\\\",\\n      \\\"action_type\\\": \\\"pr\\\",\\n      \\\"action_description\\\": \\\"PR #123\\\",\\n      \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/123\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"test\\\": \\\"TestRewindToCheckpoint\\\",\\n      \\\"agents\\\": [\\\"all\\\"],\\n      \\\"classification\\\": \\\"real-bug\\\",\\n      \\\"action_type\\\": \\\"issue\\\",\\n      \\\"action_description\\\": \\\"Issue #456 (new)\\\",\\n      \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://github.com/entireio/cli/issues/456\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe workflow's \\\"Build Slack summary\\\" step reads this JSON and formats it into a Slack Block Kit message.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `.github/workflows/e2e-triage.yml` | Add 3 steps: Slack start notification, build summary, Slack complete notification |\\n| `.claude/skills/e2e-triage/SKILL.md` | Add `triage-summary.json` output requirement to Step 7 |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. Push to a branch and verify workflow YAML parses correctly in GitHub Actions UI\\n2. Test the \\\"Build Slack summary\\\" step locally by creating a sample `triage-summary.json` and running the jq formatting\\n3. Full end-to-end: trigger a manual E2E run, let it fail, verify both Slack messages appear\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.claude/projects/-Users-alisha-Projects-devenv-cli/a3480680-037a-4f32-90f3-99642180a443.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"701b64d8-849a-4bd8-a37d-1228d797bec2\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T19:53:25.436Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Slack Notifications for E2E Triage\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe E2E triage automation (already implemented) downloads CI artifacts, classifies failures, and creates PRs/issues. Currently, when E2E tests fail, Slack gets a failure notification from `e2e.yml` — but there's no follow-up telling the team that Claude is triaging or what the outcome was. This plan adds two Slack messages from the triage workflow:\\n\\n1. **\\\"Claude is triaging...\\\"** — posted when triage starts\\n2. **\\\"Triage complete: PR #X, Issue #Y\\\"** — posted when triage finishes with links to actions taken\\n\\n## Constrain